==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dagon
<hw>Da"gon</hw> <pr>(d⟦amac⟧"g⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <ety>[Heb.
<ets>D⟦amac⟧gon</ets>, fr. <ets>dag</ets> a fish: cf. Gr.
<grk>Dagw`n</grk>.]</ety> <def>The national god of the Philistines,
represented with the face and hands and upper part of a man, and the
tail of a fish.</def> <rj><au>W. Smith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This day a solemn feast the people hold⟦br⟧
To <qex>Dagon</qex>, their sea idol.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They brought it into the house of <qex>Dagon</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1
Sam. v. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dagon</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dagon
<hw>Dag"on</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧g"⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Dag</er> a loose end.]</ety> <def>A slip or piece.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dagswain</ent>⟦br⟧
